@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

top to bottom direction
title FIG-08-04. Online Store order data flow

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 75
skinparam ranksep 55

rectangle "Customer\n<<External entity>>" as Customer #FFFFFF
rectangle "Capture order\n<<Process>>" as Capture #EAF6E8
rectangle "Authorise payment\n<<Process>>" as PaymentProcess #EAF6E8
rectangle "Create shipment request\n<<Process>>" as ShipmentProcess #EAF6E8
database "Order data\n<<Data store>>" as OrderStore #F2F5F7
rectangle "Payment Provider System\n<<External system>>" as PaymentProvider #FFF4D6
rectangle "Delivery Partner System\n<<External system>>" as DeliveryPartner #FFF4D6
rectangle "Payment authorisation request\n<<Data flow>>" as PaymentRequest #FFFFFF
rectangle "Payment authorisation result\n<<Data flow>>" as PaymentResult #FFFFFF
rectangle "Shipment request\n<<Data flow>>" as ShipmentRequest #FFFFFF
rectangle "Shipment confirmation\nand tracking data\n<<Data flow>>" as ShipmentConfirmation #FFFFFF

Customer --> Capture : Order details
Capture --> PaymentProcess : Order total
PaymentProcess --> ShipmentProcess : Paid order

PaymentProcess -right-> PaymentRequest
PaymentRequest -right-> PaymentProvider
PaymentProvider -down-> PaymentResult
PaymentResult -left-> PaymentProcess

ShipmentProcess -right-> ShipmentRequest
ShipmentRequest -right-> DeliveryPartner
DeliveryPartner -down-> ShipmentConfirmation
ShipmentConfirmation -left-> ShipmentProcess

Capture --> OrderStore : Order draft
PaymentProcess --> OrderStore : Payment status
ShipmentProcess --> OrderStore : Shipment status

note bottom
  DFD view.
  Arrows show data movement and transformation, not process sequence ownership,
  database schema or software deployment.
end note
@enduml
